DEFINITIONS

"The Game" refers to Cubon, developed by Cotordo Games, including all official
releases, updates, and associated content.

"The Codebase" refers to the source code, scripts, and engine logic contained
within this repository.

"Non-Code Assets" refers to all assets that are not source code, including but
not limited to: artwork, sprites, tilesets, music, sound effects, voice acting,
story content, character designs, and world/level data belonging to The Game.

"Protected Elements" refers to the following specific components of The Game
which are considered core to its identity and are explicitly protected under
this license:
  - All playable characters, including Cubon, King Cubit, Johnny, and any
    other named characters appearing in The Game
  - All levels, zones, and world structures as designed in The Game
  - The Game's story, script, dialogue, and narrative structure
  - All original music and sound effects produced for The Game
  - All original sprite and tile artwork produced for The Game

"Substantially Reproduces" means any Derivative Work or project that
recreates or incorporates 50% or more of any one or more Protected Elements,
regardless of whether the assets used are original or recreated from scratch.
Deliberate near-identical recreation of Protected Elements to circumvent this
threshold is also considered a violation.

"Derivative Work" refers to any project, tool, game, or software that is based
on, incorporates, or is derived from The Codebase.

"Monetization" refers to any form of direct financial gain tied to a specific
project, including but not limited to: selling the project, placing it behind
a paywall, running advertisements within or alongside it, or soliciting
donations explicitly tied to that project (e.g. a Patreon post, crowdfunding
campaign, or donation link that names or promotes the project as a reward or
incentive). General creator support platforms (e.g. a personal Patreon) are
not considered Monetization unless the project is listed as a perk, goal, or
incentive.

"You" refers to any individual or entity accessing, using, or modifying The
Codebase.

